cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MA, cs.DS

This paper discusses the spatial patterns of base stations in cellular networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves statistical analysis and modeling, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the use of stochastic geometry models and point processes indicates a potential fit for cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
